TEVA this is worse than tobaccoWhen opioid painkillers are hard to come by those who suffer from opioid dependency often turn to heroin as a comparable alternative As a result the increase in opioid dependency in the US has also triggered an increase in heroin addiction with three out of four new heroin users reporting using prescription opioids prior to heroin according to the CDC

TEVA The number of opioid overdose deaths recorded in the US has quadrupled since 1999 with prescription painkillers being the driving force behind the uptick according to the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention Similar to the rise in overdoses the amount of prescription opioids sold to pharmacies and medical practitioners including drugs such as oxycodone hydrocodone and methadone also nearly quadrupled between 1999 and 2010 the CDC found
